{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2517","heading":"Authority for certain personnel","label":"2517 Authority for certain personnel","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/stII/ch25/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of the Coast Guard Authorization Act of 2025, referred to in subsec. (c), is the date of enactment of div. G of , which was approved .Pub. L. 119–60Dec. 18, 2025"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any category of medical or health professional positions within the Coast Guard.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any childcare services position.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any position in the Coast Guard housing office of a Coast Guard installation, the primary function of which is supervision of Coast Guard housing covered by subchapter III of chapter 29 of this title.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any nonclinical specialist position the purpose of which is the integrated primary prevention of harmful behavior, including suicide, sexual assault, harassment, domestic abuse, and child abuse.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any special agent position of the Coast Guard Investigative Service.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any civilian faculty member appointed under section 1941.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/a/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fa%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A position involving the improvement of cadet health or well-being.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Limitation","label":"b .—Limitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Commandant shall only appoint qualified candidates under the authority provided by subsections (a) and (b) if the Commandant determines that there is a shortage of qualified candidates for the positions described in such subsection or a critical hiring need for such positions.1So in original.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Briefing Requirement","label":"c .—Briefing Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of employees hired under the authority provided under this section within the year for which the briefing is provided.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The positions and grades for which employees were hired.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A justification for the Commandant’s determination that such positions involved a shortage of qualified candidates or a critical hiring need.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of employees who were hired under the authority provided under this section who have separated from the Coast Guard.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Steps the Coast Guard has taken to engage with the Office of Personnel Management under subpart B of part 337 of title 5, Code of Federal Regulations, for positions for which the Commandant determines a direct hire authority remains necessary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Sunset","label":"d .—Sunset","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2517","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2517%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The authority provided under subsection (a) shall expire on .September 30, 2030","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
